<title>UK: First Leisure firms on Rank bid talk.</title>
<headline>First Leisure firms on Rank bid talk.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in First Leisure Plc were boosted on Tuesday by market talk that the company could be the target of a bid from Rank Group Plc.</p>
<p>The shares were 17-1/2p higher at 351-1/2 by 0954 GMT.</p>
<p>&quot;There's been some talk that Rank may bid for them and that has firmed up the price, but I don't know how many people are taking it seriously,&quot; one dealer said.</p>
<p>A spokesman for Rank said the company never commented on market rumours.</p>
<p>-- Andrew Marshall, London newsroom +44 171 542 4026</p>
